title: Un bus convencional perdi√≥ el control y casi cae al abismo
text:
Bucaramanga
Un bus que transitaba por la calle 45 en inmediaciones del barrio Campohermoso de Bucaramanga, perdi√≥ el control y por poco cae a un abismo.
En unas fotograf√≠as que circulan en redes sociales, se observa como el veh√≠culo sobrepas√≥ el anden, rompi√≥ las mallas de seguridad de la v√≠a y por poco ocasiona una tragedia.
El nuevo secretario del interior en Bucaramanga ser√° el coronel retirado Giraldo Rayo
De acuerdo con reportes de las autoridades y de la comunidad m√°s cercana, no se registraron heridos de gravedad sin embargo, la emergencia que ocasion√≥ un fuerte susto a los pasajeros, dej√≥ dos personas levemente heridas quienes fueron trasladadas a la Cl√≠nica Bucaramanga.

author: Isabelle Parkin
title: Watch: Tiger cub who used walking aids in first few weeks of life marks first birthday at West Midlands Safari Park | Express & Star
text: Watch: Tiger cub who used walking aids in first few weeks of life marks first birthday at West Midlands Safari Park A critically endangered tiger cub at West Midlands Safari Park who had to a tough start to life has celebrated her first birthday. Watch more of our videos on Shots! and live on Freeview channel 276 Lestari made history when she was born at the attraction in [Bewdley](https://www.expressandstar.com/news/local-hubs/wyre-forest/bewdley) on July 4 last year to mum, Dourga, and dad, Nakal, becoming the first Sumatran cub to arrive there. But when she was just four weeks old, keepers at the park noticed a weakness in her front limbs which was affecting her development. Joined by the veterinary team, they decided to step in and set up a three-week long physiotherapy programme, involving exercises and using walking aids to help strengthen her legs. Their hard work paid off and a year later, Lestari can run, leap and bound her enclosure. To celebrate the one-year milestone, keepers put together a birthday fest for the young tiger including a cake made from frozen goat‚Äôs milk, chunks of meat and some shaped, blood ice blocks. Lestari further marked the special occasion by playing with some of her favourite toys. Head keeper of carnivores at [West Midlands Safari Park](https://www.wmsp.co.uk/?gad_source=1&gclid=CjwKCAjwkJm0BhBxEiwAwT1AXBW8y3S7wbInIyRR_80BggZfdkDsZLTqVmkhHJsgywj8nxxhTje2uRoCyvMQAvD_BwE), Chris Hodgkins, said: "When Lestari arrived a year ago, the keepers and I were over the moon. "However, we started to notice something wasn‚Äôt quite right with her legs and so our vet team had to step in, to carry out daily physiotherapy to aid her walking. ‚ÄúThe physio was a success and Lestari has gone from strength to strength since. This has created a very special bond with us all and to see her progress and become stronger every day, has been very rewarding.‚Äù Mr Hodgkins described the tiger cub as "active" and "mischievous" and said though independent at times, she never wanders from from her mum's side. He added: "The keepers worked really hard to ensure a very easy introduction with her dad, Nakal, who she has also bonded extremely well with. "We often see her playing with Nakal and giving him a good run around. It is amazing to see that our efforts a year ago have paid off and we‚Äôre all very proud of the young tiger Lestari has become.‚Äù Sumatran tigers are classed as ‚Äòcritically endangered‚Äô, which means there is an extremely high likelihood they could face extinction in the near future. There are estimated to be fewer than 400 individuals left in the wild and numbers seem to be decreasing. Visitors to the safari park can spot Lestari with her parents in Tiger Tropics, located in the walk-through area. More information can be found [on the attraction's website](http://www.wmsp.co.uk).

title: Acuerdan ayuda humanitaria por llegada de caravana de 5 mil migrantes a Oaxaca, la m√°s numerosa del a√±o | Oaxaca
text: Acuerdan ayuda humanitaria por llegada de caravana de 5 mil migrantes a Oaxaca, la m√°s numerosa del a√±o Autoridades federales y estatales se reunieron en Juchit√°n para acordar las medidas pertinentes, pues se estima que los miles de extranjeros podr√≠an llegar a territorio estatal este fin de semana [Sociedad](https://oaxaca.eluniversal.com.mx/secciones/sociedad)28/12/2023 14:44 Alberto L√≥pez Morales / Corresponsal Actualizada 14:44 Juchit√°n.‚Äî Autoridades federales y estatales en Oaxaca acordaron ayer una serie de acciones para recibir a la caravana de migrantes, procedentes de Tapachula, Chiapas, en caso de que ingresen al territorio oaxaque√±o, como ha ocurrido en anteriores ocasiones. Representantes de la Secretar√≠a de Gobernaci√≥n (Segob) y de la Secretar√≠a de Gobierno de Oaxaca (Sego) se reunieron por la tarde-noche de ayer mi√©rcoles en la sede que tiene la Guardia Nacional (GN), en la ciudad de Juchit√°n, donde valoraron la atenci√≥n humanitaria que prestar√°n. La caravana, compuesta por m√°s de cinco mil migrantes de diferentes nacionalidades, viene caminando sobre la carretera Panamericana en el subtramo Tapanatepec-Talism√°n y se espera que arribe hoy a Mapastepec, para avanzar ma√±ana hacia Pijijiapan. De acuerdo con asistentes a la reuni√≥n de ayer, en la que participaron enviados de los Servicios de Salud (SSO) y de Protecci√≥n Civil, as√≠ como de la Defensa Nacional y de la GN, la primera medida ser√° garantizar la atenci√≥n humanitaria hacia los migrantes. Las autoridades estiman que si la caravana avanza al mismo ritmo de los √∫ltimos d√≠as, podr√≠a estar ingresando el domingo al territorio oaxaque√±o, a partir de su recorrido de Pijijiapan, Tonal√° y Arriaga, Chiapas e ingresar a Los Corazones, de San Pedro Tapanatepec. ‚ÄúVamos a estar pendientes del recorrido y cuando entren al territorio de Oaxaca, se desplegar√°n brigadas m√©dicas para atender principalmente a mujeres y ni√±os, y vigilaremos el trayecto para garantizar la seguridad de los migrantes‚Äù, dijo una fuente del gobierno oaxaque√±o a EL UNIVERSAL. Esta caravana, de acuerdo con las propias autoridades federales y estatales, es la m√°s numerosa de todas las que han ingresado al territorio oaxaque√±o en este a√±o, donde ante el intenso flujo migratorio, el gobierno federal habilit√≥ un Centro de Movilidad Migratorio (CMM), en Juchit√°n. De acuerdo con estimaciones de las autoridades, tan solo de junio a noviembre de este a√±o, han cruzado el territorio oaxaque√±o poco m√°s de 700 mil migrantes, en su ruta hacia la frontera norte de nuestro pa√≠s, con destino a los Estados Unidos. Esta reuni√≥n se da luego de que durante el tr√°nsito de la caravana anterior en noviembre pasado, los migrantes denunciaron una serie de abusos de parte de autoridades oaxaque√±as, mientras que ediles de la regi√≥n del Istmo de Tehuantepec se negaron a brindar ayuda humanitaria e incluso cayeron en pr√°cticas discriminatorias y de xenofobia.

author: Abbas Adil
title: India bans J&K Muslim League faction - Shafaqna India | Indian Shia News Agency
text: India designated the Muslim League Jammu Kashmir (Masarat Alam faction), or MLJK-MA, as an unlawful association under the Unlawful Activities Prevention law, the Scroll news portal said. The Muslim League Jammu Kashmir (Masarat Alam faction) is a separatist organisation led by Hurriyat Conference chairman Masarat Alam Bhat, who is imprisoned in Delhi‚Äôs Tihar Jail. The Scroll quoted Home Minister Amit Shah as saying in a social media post that the organisation and its members are involved in ‚Äúanti-national and secessionist activities in Jammu and Kashmir supporting terrorist activities and inciting people to establish Islamic rule‚Äù in the Union Territory. ‚ÄúThe Prime Minister Narendra Modi government‚Äôs message is loud and clear that anyone acting against the unity, sovereignty, and integrity of our nation will not be spared and face the full wrath of the law,‚Äù wrote Shah. The home ministry, in a notification, said that the leaders of the organisation have been involved in raising funds through various sources, including Pakistan and its proxy organisations, ‚Äúfor perpetrating unlawful activities‚Äù. The ministry said that Bhat has been involved in unlawful activities, which are ‚Äúprejudicial to the integrity, sovereignty, security and communal harmony of the country‚Äù. It also said that the Central government believes that the Muslim League Jammu Kashmir (Masarat Alam faction) will continue propagating ‚Äúfalse narratives‚Äù and anti-national sentiments among the people of Jammu and Kashmir if there is no immediate curb or control of their activities.

title: Woman who 'died' in coma says psychic pal brought her back to earth to finish 'mission'
text: A woman who ‚Äúdied‚Äù in a [coma ](https://www.dailystar.co.uk/latest/hospital)says she was brought back to Earth by a [psychic ](https://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/latest-news/asparagus-psychic-who-predicted-queens-31770154)pal to ‚Äúfinish her mission‚Äù. Kirsty Bortoft was found unresponsive on the sofa by her husband Stu when they were preparing to go out on a date together on January 29, 2021. After being rushed to hospital, medics told her loved ones she had a 6% chance of survival. But despite all the odds, the 49-year-old managed to pull through and now has revealed what she found while she was seemingly gone. She said: ‚ÄúThe first night was crucial and it wasn‚Äôt looking good, where Stu was told he should prepare for me not making it ‚Äì but he wasn‚Äôt having any of it.‚Äù READ MORE: [Prince Harry and Meghan will divorce and this is where kids will go, says psychic](https://www.dailystar.co.uk/news/latest-news/psychics-predict-harry-meghan-divorce-31655421) For the latest news and updates from the Royal Family, click [here](https://www.dailystar.co.uk/latest/royal-family). The mum of three battled through multiple cardiac arrests and after her heart stopped beating for 40 minutes, she was placed into a medically-induced coma. Kirsty continued: ‚ÄúNo one at this point knew what was going on apart from my immediate family, but my psychic friend got in touch with my sister and asked what was going on. She said my spirit was in her front room and I was asking her to write lists for my boys and dad. ‚ÄúI told [my friend] that my body was breaking down and I didn‚Äôt think I could back get into it, but she got stern with me and told me to go back. Meanwhile, in the hospital, my family were being told to prepare themselves for the end.‚Äù When the decision was made to bring her back from the coma, Kirsty immediately asked for Stu. Her lungs and heart were found to have barely any damage on scans just weeks later, only adding to the miracle. Kirsty said: ‚ÄúI recall upon finally coming back in to my body, that I knew exactly what I needed to do to heal, like a download of information. I realised you don‚Äôt die, only your body moves on and that my mission here wasn‚Äôt over yet. I told the doctor I healed my lungs and he asked how, so I shared my story. I left feeling elated and excited about my recovery.‚Äù For the latest breaking news from the Royal Family and stories from the Daily Star, sign up for our newsletter by clicking [here](https://www.dailystar.co.uk/newsletter-preference-centre/).

title: Demir√∂ren's credit arrears to Ziraat Bank exceed 25 million dollars, Court of Accounts reveals
text: Demir√∂ren's credit arrears to Ziraat Bank exceed 25 million dollars, Court of Accounts reveals Pro-government Demir√∂ren Holding‚Äôs credit arrears to state-run Ziraat Bank have exceeded 25 million dollars, a report by the Turkish Court of Accounts revealed. The company's total debt to the bank due to this credit reached 920 million dollars as of December, 2022. Duvar English The credit arrears of Demir√∂ren Holding, Turkey‚Äôs largest media owner, to state-run Ziraat Bank have exceeded 25 million dollars at the end of 2022, according to the Turkish Court of Account reports. The Holding continued not paying the credit in 2022 despite restructuring the payment twice, the online news outlet T24 [reported](https://t24.com.tr/haber/ziraat-e-borcunu-yapilandirmisti-demiroren-2022-de-de-odeme-yapmamis,1145138) on Dec. 28. According to the Court of Account report, the Demir√∂ren Holding did not act in accordance with the credit payment plans, even though the 800 million dollar credit acquired from Ziraat Bank to purchase Doƒüan Media Group was restructured for 14 years. While the Holding paid only 586 million liras during the year, its total debt to the bank due to this credit reached 920 million dollars as of Dec. 31, 2022. Within the scope of the practice of not including company names in Court of Accounts reports, Demir√∂ren Holding's name was not mentioned in the report. As in the 2021 report, April 5, 2018 was mentioned as the start date of the credit relationship with the company, which revealed that the report was about Demir√∂ren Holding. Pro-government Demir√∂ren in 2018 paid $916 million for H√ºrriyet newspaper, broadcaster CNN T√ºrk and other assets from Doƒüan Holding. The deal shifted the mainstream media overwhelmingly behind President Recep Tayyip Erdoƒüan.
